arXiv:2503.10176v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We prove the uniform Lyndon interpolation property (ULIP) of some extensions of the pure logic of necessitation $\mathbf{N}$. For any $m, n \in \mathbb{N}$, $\mathbf{N}^+\mathbf{A}_{m,n}$ is the logic obtained from $\mathbf{N}$ by adding a single axiom $\Box^n \varphi 	o \Box^m \varphi$, which is a $\Diamond$-free modal reduction principle, and a rule $ rac{
eg \Box \varphi}{
eg \Box \Box \varphi}$, which is required to make the logic complete with respect to its Kripke-like semantics. We first introduce a sequent calculus $\mathbf{GN}^+\mathbf{A}_{m,n}$ for $\mathbf{N}^+\mathbf{A}_{m,n}$ and show that it enjoys cut elimination, proving Craig and Lyndon interpolation properties as a consequence. We then construct an embedding of $\mathbf{N}^+\mathbf{A}_{m,n}$ into classical propositional logic $\mathbf{Cl}$, which is then used to prove ULIP of $\mathbf{N}^+\mathbf{A}_{m,n}$ by reducing it to that of $\mathbf{Cl}$. We also prove ULIP of $\mathbf{NRA}_{m,n} = \mathbf{N} + \Box^n \varphi 	o \Box^m \varphi +  rac{
eg \varphi}{
eg \Box \varphi}$ with a similar method.
